HEADWORD: Efflate
<hw>Ef*flate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>efflatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>efflare</ets> to blow or breathe out;
<ets>ex</ets> + <ets>flare</ets> to blow.]</ety> <def>To fill with
breath; to puff up.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

